 Plateau State Governor and Chairman, Northern Governors Forum, Simon Lalong, has congratulated acting President of the Court of Appeal, Justice Monica Dongban-Mensem on the confirmation of her appointment by the Senate and the occasion of her 63rd birthday. Lalong, in a congratulatory message, described Justice Dongban-Mensem as a highly-blessed woman who has devoted her life to the service of humanity and promotion of justice, peace and progress. A statement by his Director of Press and Public Affairs, Dr. Makut Simon Macham, reads: “This is a special moment in your life where you need to reflect on the mercies of God and thank him for not only sustaining you and your family, but also lifting you to the position of the President, Court of Appeal. As you add more years, we pray that God will give you wisdom, patience and boldness to serve the nation with diligence, sincerity and fairness”. Lalong noted that over the years, Justice Dongban-Mensem has left the legacy of excellence and humility in all the places she had worked as well as a positive impression on the people she had dealings with. Lalong assured her that Nigerians and in particular the people of Plateau State would continue to pray for her.  He also reminded her of the need to continue her humanitarian services and also seek God’s direction at all times. 